sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant TG as Telegram Bot
    participant API as API Gateway
    participant US as User Service
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    
    Note over U,DB: Scenario 1: First-time Telegram login
    
    U->>TG: Opens WebApp
    TG->>U: Sends initData (id, first_name, hash)
    U->>API: POST /auth/telegram
    API->>US: Validate & authenticate
    
    US->>US: Validate hash
    US->>DB: SELECT * WHERE credentials->'telegram'->>'id' = '123456789'
    DB-->>US: User not found
    
    US->>DB: INSERT INTO users (credentials = {'telegram': {...}})
    DB-->>US: User created
    
    US->>US: Create session token
    US-->>API: {user_id, session_token, role}
    API-->>U: Authenticated ✓
    
    Note over U,DB: Scenario 2: Existing Telegram user adds web login
    
    U->>API: POST /users/me/web-credentials
    API->>US: Add web auth
    
    US->>DB: SELECT * WHERE id = user_id
    DB-->>US: User with telegram credentials
    
    US->>US: user.set_web_credentials(email, password_hash)
    US->>DB: UPDATE users SET credentials = credentials || {'web': {...}}
    DB-->>US: Updated
    
    US-->>API: Web credentials added ✓
    API-->>U: You can now login with email
    
    Note over U,DB: Scenario 3: Multi-platform login (user has both)
    
    U->>API: POST /auth/web (email, password)
    API->>US: Authenticate
    
    US->>DB: SELECT * WHERE credentials->'web'->>'email' = 'john@example.com'
    DB-->>US: User found (has both telegram & web)
    
    US->>US: Verify password_hash
    US->>US: Create session token
    US-->>API: {user_id, session_token, platforms: ['telegram', 'web']}
    API-->>U: Authenticated ✓
